02:09.896 --> 02:12.431
Damn, Freddie.

02:12.433 --> 02:15.367
Seeing you out here is like
seeing a fish ride a bicycle.

02:15.369 --> 02:17.336
What are you doing here?

02:17.338 --> 02:19.338
We got real issues, Steve.

02:19.340 --> 02:20.873
How'd you find me?

02:20.875 --> 02:22.708
How is that
even important right now?

02:22.710 --> 02:24.493
Important to me.

02:24.494 --> 02:26.277
Who cares? I'm here,
and we got issues.

02:27.681 --> 02:28.747
Stop leaning.

02:28.749 --> 02:30.315
-Leaning?
-On the car.

02:30.317 --> 02:31.817
-You're leaning on the car.
-Oh, Christ, Steve.

02:31.819 --> 02:34.620
Listen to me,
we need to talk about France.

02:34.622 --> 02:36.455
-What about it?
- Word's out.

02:36.457 --> 02:38.824
Talk's all over town,
and it's not good.

02:38.826 --> 02:41.426
Not my problem anymore.
I'm done.

02:41.428 --> 02:44.329
Yeah, maybe when your name
is Joe Schmoe from Buttonwillow,

02:44.331 --> 02:46.832
not when your name
is Steve fucking McQueen.

02:46.834 --> 02:49.401
Cinema Center reps
are not happy, Steve.

02:49.403 --> 02:51.203
So what's the brass tax?

02:51.205 --> 02:52.538
They want you to do press.

02:52.540 --> 02:54.173
-No.
-Steve...

02:54.175 --> 02:56.909
Look, the point was to make
a good film. A real film.

02:56.911 --> 03:00.379
People like a story, Steve.
They like characters.

03:00.381 --> 03:02.414
You were shooting
a two-hour documentary

03:02.416 --> 03:05.417
about a car race that
nobody in America cares about!

03:05.419 --> 03:07.586
We'd made them care.
The suits thought different.

03:08.322 --> 03:09.521
I'm done with it.

03:09.523 --> 03:11.857
Fine. I'll go back
to Rosen with that.

03:11.859 --> 03:13.525
But it's not gonna
go down too well.

03:13.527 --> 03:15.761
And it still doesn't change
where we are now.

03:15.763 --> 03:17.663
We have to do
some damage control.

03:17.665 --> 03:19.198
Damage control?

03:19.200 --> 03:21.667
- Bill called me.
-Ah, son of a bitch.

03:21.669 --> 03:23.302
We're your team, Steve,
all right?

03:23.304 --> 03:25.771
If we don't communicate,
this doesn't work.

03:25.773 --> 03:28.740
We're not the enemy.
Just let us do our job.

03:28.742 --> 03:30.826
It's time to go to work.

03:30.827 --> 03:32.911
You need to chose
your next picture carefully.

03:32.913 --> 03:35.280
I'm doing
On Any Sunday with Bruce.

03:35.282 --> 03:37.683
The motorcycle thing?

03:37.685 --> 03:40.586
No, that's a vacation.
You need a paycheck.

03:40.588 --> 03:42.454
I might have some
endorsements lined up.

03:42.456 --> 03:44.323
Strictly overseas.

03:44.325 --> 03:46.992
But our top priority
has to be your next gig.

03:46.994 --> 03:49.394
Something to put you
back on top.

03:49.396 --> 03:52.431
Have you thought about
what I said about First Artists?

03:52.433 --> 03:53.799
Just join the club, huh?

03:53.801 --> 03:55.834
Yeah, it's a good deal.

03:55.836 --> 03:57.769
And Newman, what's he doing?

03:58.706 --> 04:01.373
For First Artists? Pocket money.

04:03.811 --> 04:04.910
Come on.
You're already attached.

04:04.912 --> 04:06.778
You're the pick
of the litter already.

04:06.780 --> 04:09.948
Junior Bonner, The Getaway,
that French prison thing.

04:09.950 --> 04:11.016
Just pick.

04:12.753 --> 04:14.286
Ah, just pick, huh?

04:14.288 --> 04:15.354
Yeah.

04:20.261 --> 04:21.593
Just pick.

04:21.595 --> 04:23.262
Yeah, Steve, pick!
For Christ's...

04:23.264 --> 04:25.030
I came all the way out
to bumblefuck here

04:25.032 --> 04:26.832
to tell you things are bad.

04:26.834 --> 04:28.400
You hemorrhage your money,
and you burn

04:28.402 --> 04:30.369
every goddamn bridge
back in France.

04:31.705 --> 04:33.538
You know what's really
chapping my hide, Freddie?

04:35.676 --> 04:37.576
This car.

04:37.577 --> 04:39.477
Who cares? They come
and go with you, Steve.

04:39.480 --> 04:40.879
Yeah,
Warner Brothers gave it to me.

04:40.881 --> 04:42.514
A gift.

04:42.516 --> 04:43.782
It's a beauty.

04:43.784 --> 04:45.651
Yeah. There's just one problem.

04:45.653 --> 04:47.419
What's the problem, Haig?

04:47.421 --> 04:48.654
It's not the car.

04:48.656 --> 04:49.788
It's not the car.

04:50.391 --> 04:51.723
What car?

04:51.725 --> 04:52.891
The car.

04:53.794 --> 04:55.778
Ah, Christ.

04:55.779 --> 04:57.763
Look, this is a pacifier.
It... An imposter.

04:58.732 --> 05:01.533
The car was 1968 GT 390.

05:02.303 --> 05:04.503
325 horsepower,

05:04.505 --> 05:06.705
427 foot-pounds of torque.

05:06.707 --> 05:08.440
A real power plant.

05:08.442 --> 05:10.709
Had a four-speed
manual transmission too. What...

05:10.711 --> 05:11.777
What else, Haig?

05:11.779 --> 05:13.645
Dark Highland green.

05:13.647 --> 05:15.013
Dark Highland green.

05:15.015 --> 05:16.982
Who cares?

05:17.718 --> 05:18.884
Are you blind?

05:21.221 --> 05:23.555
Listen, this is
a '67 302 Boss prototype.

05:23.557 --> 05:24.956
It's no GT 390.

05:26.860 --> 05:28.527
And it's a fucking automatic.

05:31.899 --> 05:33.732
Find me the car, Freddie.

05:33.734 --> 05:35.701
Look, we don't have time
for this, Steve.

05:36.670 --> 05:38.036
It's all set, Steve.

05:38.038 --> 05:39.805
-Thanks, buddy.

05:42.910 --> 05:46.578
That's it. You find me the car,
I'll pick my next project.

05:46.580 --> 05:49.748
Look, that's gonna
be impossible.

05:49.750 --> 05:50.882
I need it, Freddie.

05:52.119 --> 05:54.453
Blink if it's a yes.

05:54.455 --> 05:57.055
-Good. Sundown oughta do it.

05:57.057 --> 05:59.624
You're a standup guy, Freddie.
I'll call to check in.

06:02.563 --> 06:05.931
"A two-hour documentary
about a car race

06:05.933 --> 06:08.100
that nobody in America
cares about"?

06:08.102 --> 06:10.102
- Their words.

06:10.104 --> 06:11.603
You've seen Katzin's cut?

06:12.773 --> 06:14.406
Most of John's stuff is out.

06:14.975 --> 06:16.041
Too bad.

06:23.784 --> 06:25.817
Be reasonable, Steve.

06:25.819 --> 06:28.587
Freddie, I hired you
to be a barracuda.

06:29.790 --> 06:31.022
Are you a barracuda?

06:34.027 --> 06:35.827
I'm a barracuda.

06:35.829 --> 06:37.596
Right. Find the car.

06:40.701 --> 06:41.833
Adios.

