in France,

10:02.302 --> 10:03.835
what's been happening.

10:06.640 --> 10:08.006
I gotta get over this.

10:08.008 --> 10:10.342
I wanna come home, believe me.

10:10.344 --> 10:12.210
I gotta... I gotta get my head
clear.

10:15.282 --> 10:16.781
We've both done things...

10:16.783 --> 10:19.217
No, you did things.
This is about what you did.

10:22.122 --> 10:23.321
Have the kids noticed?

10:25.659 --> 10:27.392
Chad is fine.
I don't think he sees this

10:27.394 --> 10:29.728
as much different
than you being on location.

10:31.331 --> 10:33.798
Terry?

10:33.800 --> 10:37.068
She's sharp. She knows
something's up. Old soul.

10:44.711 --> 10:47.012
-Have you seen a cut yet?
-No.

10:47.814 --> 10:49.147
Soon maybe?

10:49.149 --> 10:50.348
Sure. Maybe.

10:51.685 --> 10:54.219
Suppose that's up to Bob Rosen.

10:54.221 --> 10:56.788
Well, no matter what they do,
it's still your movie.

10:56.790 --> 10:58.907
Oh?

10:58.908 --> 11:01.025
I guarantee, whatever they do,
it will not be my movie.

11:01.028 --> 11:03.928
Those jackals got a grip
and started tearing away.

11:03.930 --> 11:05.930
Teeth biting right into it.

11:05.932 --> 11:07.999
Oh, there'll be nothing left
but a carcass.

11:18.779 --> 11:21.312
You know, I think William Morris
is gonna be a good fit for you.

11:23.016 --> 11:24.416
Yeah, Hilly thinks so.

11:24.418 --> 11:26.885
Yeah, well,
Hilly knows his business.

11:26.887 --> 11:28.987
He's always been there for me.

11:28.989 --> 11:30.755
This could be big for me, baby.

11:32.459 --> 11:34.726
So, what is CBS saying
about the spin-off?

11:36.930 --> 11:38.363
Not sure yet.

11:38.365 --> 11:40.398
The producers
really seem to like it.

11:40.400 --> 11:43.034
Well, I have no doubt.

11:50.744 --> 11:52.077
Have you been seeing the doctor?

11:53.213 --> 11:54.379
Yes.

11:56.983 --> 11:58.850
Is there enough food here?
I could have Ariel pick up

11:58.852 --> 11:59.918
-some essentials.

12:02.889 --> 12:03.872
I eat out.

12:03.873 --> 12:04.856
Just the thought of you
here by yourself.

12:04.858 --> 12:06.157
I'm a grown-ass man.

12:06.727 --> 12:07.792
I know.

12:11.298 --> 12:12.731
You got plans later?

12:13.433 --> 12:15.266
Figure we could go to Chez Jay.

12:17.070 --> 12:19.437
I'm going to have
a quiet night, I think.

12:19.439 --> 12:21.306
Quiet night, huh?

12:21.308 --> 12:24.442
Yes. Gonna head over to Ann's,
drink some wine.

12:24.444 --> 12:26.911
-Girl time.
-Girl time.

12:26.913 --> 12:28.413
What happens again at girl time?

12:29.983 --> 12:33.017
Just girl stuff.
You know, chat, gossip.

12:33.487 --> 12:34.753
Gossip.

12:35.155 --> 12:36.421
Chit-chat.

12:36.423 --> 12:37.956
No, you said "gossip."

12:38.959 --> 12:40.158
Figure of speech.

12:46.166 --> 12:47.432
Talk about me?

12:47.434 --> 12:49.200
Sometimes. That's what girls do.

12:50.337 --> 12:52.370
No, see, that's what
the doctor's for.

12:52.372 --> 12:54.372
You... you tell
the doctor something,

12:54.374 --> 12:56.040
and he doesn't tell anyone else.

12:57.344 --> 12:59.043
He's a doctor.

12:59.045 --> 13:01.412
It's called confidentiality.

13:01.414 --> 13:04.315
Ann, well.
Ann, she's just a person.

13:04.317 --> 13:06.851
She can flap her gums
all over town.

13:08.088 --> 13:09.254
She wouldn't do that.

13:09.256 --> 13:11.322
Oh, no. Not Ann.
Not dear old Ann.

13:12.993 --> 13:14.926
I wanna know
what you and Ann talk about.

13:15.462 --> 13:17.228
Hm?

13:17.230 --> 13:18.329
Don't do this.

13:18.331 --> 13:19.497
Let's play a game.

13:20.500 --> 13:22.000
Like a scene study.

13:23.470 --> 13:25.937
I'll... I'll play Ann, okay?

13:25.939 --> 13:27.338
You might have heard of me.

13:27.340 --> 13:29.240
You, you just...

13:29.242 --> 13:31.142
-...be yourself.

13:32.345 --> 13:33.578
I don't wanna play.

13:33.580 --> 13:34.979
Oh, but you will.

13:35.348 --> 13:36.514
Steve...

13:37.250 --> 13:38.516
Tell me about him.

13:40.520 --> 13:41.986
Tell me about you.

13:44.591 --> 13:46.024
Not much to tell.

13:47.928 --> 13:50.094
Certainly a man like you...

13:51.264 --> 13:52.397
A man like me?

13:54.000 --> 13:55.533
A man of your position.

13:56.503 --> 13:57.936
My position.

13:59.840 --> 14:01.406
Your stature.

14:01.408 --> 14:04.075
You're a movie star, Steve.

14:04.077 --> 14:07.946
Surely, it comes
with its own set of burdens.

14:18.124 --> 14:20.458
This process only works
if you talk to me, Steve.

14:24.965 --> 14:26.531
Should I lay on the couch
or something?

14:27.901 --> 14:29.033
If you like.

14:30.036 --> 14:31.603
Nah, I'm good.

14:31.605 --> 14:33.171
All right. Let's start
from the beginning.

14:33.974 --> 14:35.240
Where were you born?

14:35.242 --> 14:37.308
Beech Grove, Indiana.

14:37.310 --> 14:39.077
Raised in Slater, Missouri.

14:40.914 --> 14:42.180
Tell me about your parents.

14:45.018 --> 14:46.084
Dead.

14:46.920 --> 14:48.286
Who were they?

14:48.288 --> 14:50.021
William and Julian McQueen.

14:51.958 --> 14:53.124
So tell me about them.

14:56.263 --> 14:58.129
Uh, this is ridiculous.

14:58.131 --> 15:00.265
I'm not paying you to sit here
and talk about them.

15:00.267 --> 15:02.333
This is supposed to be
about Neile and me.

15:02.335 --> 15:04.152
That's it.

15:04.153 --> 15:05.970
Are you uncomfortable
talking about your parents?

15:05.972 --> 15:08.306
No, I'm just peachy.

15:08.308 --> 15:10.275
There's no other place
I'd rather be right now.

15:11.678 --> 15:13.144
What would you rather be doing?

15:17.384 --> 15:18.917
Talk to me about your acting.

15:19.920 --> 15:21.386
It can get a little candy-ass.

15:22.656 --> 15:24.155
You must enjoy it, though.

15:25.492 --> 15:26.925
I enjoy the bread.

15:29.029 --> 15:30.662
How does it feel
to be a movie star?

15:33.333 --> 15:36.234
Pressure to succeed? No privacy?

15:36.236 --> 15:37.936
Look, Doc, I agreed to come here

15:37.938 --> 15:39.437
'cause I'm trying
to save my marriage.

15:39.439 --> 15:42.674
My melon, I...
I get it. It's twisted.

15:42.676 --> 15:44.309
It's just these questions.

15:44.311 --> 15:46.077
I don't know, I don't know
what you're getting at.

15:47.113 --> 15:48.980
We're trying to
get to all of it, Steve.

15:49.649 --> 15:51.449
We start at the foundation.

15:51.451 --> 15:53.117
What does my job have
to do with it?

15:54.955 --> 15:57.021
It's not just a job, Steve.

15:57.958 --> 15:59.290
You'd have to agree with that.

16:00.961 --> 16:02.527
It's the fame.

16:02.529 --> 16:03.695
The drugs.

16:04.698 --> 16:07.265
Extramarital encounters.

16:07.267 --> 16:09.701
I mean, wouldn't you agree?

16:11.037 --> 16:12.637
It's not a normal job.

16:12.639 --> 16:15.707
You're right, Doc.
When you're right, you're right.

16:15.709 --> 16:17.976
It's not a normal job.

16:20.714 --> 16:22.246
It's a fucking gas.

16:37.697 --> 16:38.997
Well, I guess

16:38.999 --> 16:40.665
today's my lucky day.

16:46.039 --> 16:47.472
Steve McQueen.

16:48.274 --> 16:49.607
Where you headed?

16:49.609 --> 16:51.275
Steve McQueen.

16:52.445 --> 16:53.544
That's me.

16:54.681 --> 16:57.515
The girls in Weedpatch
would die.

16:57.517 --> 16:59.550
Which, actually,
would be fine by me.

17:00.420 --> 17:01.652
Weedpatch?

17:01.654 --> 17:03.388
Weedpatch, California.

17:05.157 --> 17:06.424
Bakersfield.

17:06.425 --> 17:08.726
-Yeah.
-Consider it the ass end.

17:08.728 --> 17:10.395
So you coming or going?

17:11.564 --> 17:13.263
Oh, I'm going.

17:13.266 --> 17:15.433
I'm definitely going.

17:15.435 --> 17:17.702
Weedpatch is no place
for a girl like me.

17:19.204 --> 17:20.304
A black girl?

17:21.508 --> 17:23.741
Steve McQueen,
a girl with talent.

17:26.046 --> 17:27.345
So what's your angle?

17:27.347 --> 17:28.512
No angle.

17:28.515 --> 17:30.782
I'm a dancer.

17:30.784 --> 17:32.350
And when I say dancer,
I don't mean

17:32.352 --> 17:34.085
"Sunday, come-to-meetin',
cut up a rug

17:34.087 --> 17:35.720
at a sock hop" dancer.

17:35.722 --> 17:38.089
I'm a real dancer,
Steve McQueen.

