38:52.898 --> 38:54.030
Sexy.

38:55.033 --> 38:56.499
Romantic.

38:58.070 --> 39:00.370
An escape from the every day.

39:00.372 --> 39:01.938
That's what I like.

39:01.940 --> 39:03.573
Like that's what I wanna give.

39:06.378 --> 39:09.112
So, you get to New York,
then what?

39:10.415 --> 39:12.082
How do you get to Carnegie Hall?

39:15.854 --> 39:17.587
Okay, if it doesn't happen?

39:17.589 --> 39:19.122
Well, was that
ever an option of you?

39:19.124 --> 39:20.390
Never.

39:20.392 --> 39:23.360
Well then, there you go.

39:23.362 --> 39:25.695
It's just, you know,
these cities, LA, New York,

39:25.697 --> 39:28.531
they chew up gals like you.
Chew 'em up and spit 'em out.

39:28.533 --> 39:29.899
Let 'em try.

39:29.901 --> 39:32.635
I'm better off
than I was a minute ago.

39:32.637 --> 39:35.505
I'm better off every second
I'm away from Weedpatch.

39:36.608 --> 39:38.808
There's no going back.

39:38.810 --> 39:41.010
Every girl in the big city
is running away

39:41.012 --> 39:42.846
from a place like Weedpatch.

39:42.848 --> 39:44.748
Don't you think I know that,
Steve McQueen?

39:45.951 --> 39:47.817
I know what I'm up against.

39:48.954 --> 39:52.489
My skin color, my... my gender.

39:52.491 --> 39:55.158
But I choose my fate,
not anybody else.

39:56.995 --> 39:58.561
Look, I'm not... You know,

39:58.563 --> 40:00.930
I'm not trying
to make you cross.

40:00.932 --> 40:03.433
It's just,
life ain't like the movies, kid.

40:04.436 --> 40:05.635
Don't I know it?

40:16.481 --> 40:18.047
You know, I trained
with Martha Graham.

40:20.919 --> 40:23.586
You did not train
with Martha Graham.

40:23.588 --> 40:24.954
Sure did.

40:24.956 --> 40:26.589
At the Neighborhood Playhouse.

40:28.460 --> 40:29.759
You could dance?

40:29.761 --> 40:31.127
Not a lick.

40:32.798 --> 40:34.597
Why didn't you stick with it?

40:34.599 --> 40:35.865
I had my reasons.

40:37.536 --> 40:39.636
Well, I bet
you were pretty good.

40:39.638 --> 40:41.771
-We'll never know.

40:41.773 --> 40:44.474
You never wanted
to do a musical?

40:44.476 --> 40:46.776
I miss the grand MGM musicals.

40:48.647 --> 40:50.180
Nobody wants to see me do that.

40:51.983 --> 40:53.883
Jimmy Cagney did musicals.

40:55.220 --> 40:57.954
Believe me, I know. It's just...

40:57.956 --> 41:00.690
I missed that period,
you know, I...

41:00.692 --> 41:03.059
A few years earlier, maybe,
who knows? But...

41:06.465 --> 41:07.764
It didn't hurt, did it?

41:09.100 --> 41:10.867
What's that?

41:10.869 --> 41:12.202
Telling me something.

41:14.005 --> 41:16.840
Well, you're Steve McQueen.

41:17.809 --> 41:19.609
You do whatever you want.

41:19.611 --> 41:21.611
We'll see about that.

41:21.613 --> 41:24.581
Steve McQueen,
song and dance man.

41:26.618 --> 41:28.551
People just want to see you
do one thing now.

41:28.553 --> 41:30.253
They wanna see me
get the bad guy.

41:30.255 --> 41:32.722
They wanna see me,
you know, win.

41:32.724 --> 41:34.391
And there's always some kid

41:34.392 --> 41:36.059
lookin' to knock you off
the top spot.

41:36.061 --> 41:38.695
All it takes is one bad choice.

41:38.697 --> 41:40.063
I'm not gonna let that happen.

41:42.901 --> 41:44.767
Well, it could've been
a hell of a thing.

43:20.665 --> 43:22.865
No, I haven't decided yet.
I get my end first.

43:22.867 --> 43:24.233
That's the deal, remember?

43:24.235 --> 43:27.070
-Get ready to be happy.

43:27.072 --> 43:28.972
Using my considerable charm,

43:28.974 --> 43:31.841
I was able to twist some arms
over at Warner Brothers.

43:31.843 --> 43:32.976
I'm listening.

43:32.978 --> 43:34.377
Turns out Warner Brothers
sold the car

43:34.379 --> 43:36.145
to a guy named Bob Ross.

43:36.147 --> 43:38.314
Worked in
the editing department.

43:38.316 --> 43:39.882
Good stuff. You got an address?

43:46.224 --> 43:47.323
Got it.

43:48.760 --> 43:50.159
Oh, wait, Steve!

43:50.161 --> 43:52.061
I always said
you're a standup guy, Freddie.

43:52.063 --> 43:54.063
You said you'd pick a movie.

43:54.065 --> 43:55.632
When I have the keys
in hand, Freddie.

43:55.634 --> 43:56.799
Keys in hand.

43:56.801 --> 43:58.735
Steve, you son of a bitch.
Just pick...

44:00.939 --> 44:02.338
God...

44:02.340 --> 44:04.407
-Son of a bitch.

44:09.814 --> 44:12.115
Are you sure
you're gonna be okay out here?

44:12.117 --> 44:15.385
The bus'll be along in a spell.
Don't you worry.

44:17.255 --> 44:19.656
Ah, it's too bad
you're not headed to LA.

44:19.658 --> 44:21.424
That city could use
more chicks like you.

44:22.227 --> 44:24.193
No.

44:24.195 --> 44:25.895
I'm afraid this is the end
of the road

44:25.897 --> 44:28.364
for us, Steve McQueen.

44:28.366 --> 44:30.833
You know, you can
just call me Steve.

44:30.835 --> 44:32.669
There's something
about your name that just begs

44:32.671 --> 44:34.003
for it to be said together.

44:39.144 --> 44:40.410
Hey, I know people in New York.

44:40.412 --> 44:42.045
You know, maybe
I can make some calls.

44:43.448 --> 44:45.314
We both know
that's not gonna happen.

44:47.285 --> 44:48.384
Well,

44:50.889 --> 44:52.121
safe travels then.

44:54.826 --> 44:56.392
I hope you find
what you're looking for,

44:57.095 --> 44:58.161
Steve.

44:59.931 --> 45:01.764
You know, you never
told me your name.

45:08.940 --> 45:10.339
Let's play something else.

46:34.058 --> 46:35.291
That's my name.

46:52.343 --> 46:54.010
Steve McQueen.

47:15.533 --> 47:16.549
It's time to go to work.

47:16.550 --> 47:17.566
You need to chose
your next picture carefully.

47:29.848 --> 47:31.614
I didn't think you came here.

47:31.616 --> 47:33.583
Surprise.

47:33.585 --> 47:35.918
Well, since you're here,
you'd indulge me.

47:35.920 --> 47:38.254
I just thought maybe I could get
some of your thoughts on this.

47:38.256 --> 47:40.056
I'm all ears.

47:40.058 --> 47:42.091
I mean, you read
the book, right?

47:42.093 --> 47:43.392
Yeah, my wife gave it to me.

47:46.931 --> 47:50.099
It's just,
you're attached to it, I mean...

47:50.101 --> 47:51.434
You are attached to it, right?

47:51.436 --> 47:53.135
Yeah. Well,
what's your question, Dustin?

47:53.137 --> 47:55.238
Oh, I'm just intrigued. I'm...

47:56.507 --> 47:58.407
circling, you know?

47:58.409 --> 48:00.142
I think there's a great story
to be told here.

48:00.144 --> 48:01.277
I think I'm interested.

48:01.279 --> 48:02.879
In what part? Mine?

48:02.881 --> 48:05.114
No. No.

48:05.116 --> 48:06.649
Dega.

48:06.651 --> 48:09.452
-Louis Dega, the counterfeiter?
- Mm-hm.

48:09.454 --> 48:11.454
I mean, there's definitely
something there.

48:11.456 --> 48:14.590
I've been reading books
of French penal colonies.

48:14.592 --> 48:16.425
Really fascinating stuff.

48:16.427 --> 48:18.160
Any idea who they wanna direct?

48:18.162 --> 48:19.262
I think it's Schaffner.

48:22.400 --> 48:24.500
Schaffner. Interesting.

48:43.154 --> 48:46.155
Well, I'd love to know
what you think.

48:46.157 --> 48:48.090
-About what?
-About the part.

48:48.092 --> 48:50.026
Your part? It's a...
It's a fine part.

48:50.028 --> 48:51.494
No, your part.

48:51.496 --> 48:54.964
If I do this, it can't just be
another buddy picture.

48:54.966 --> 48:57.133
It needs to go much deeper.

48:59.070 --> 49:01.270
I don't know what I got
next on my plate, kid.

49:01.272 --> 49:02.571
You know, whether it's something
you wanna do,

49:02.573 --> 49:04.273
is for you to decide.

49:04.275 --> 49:07.944
Do it, don't do it.
It doesn't matter to me.

49:07.946 --> 49:09.478
On the first day of shooting,
I may see your face,

49:09.480 --> 49:11.981
I may even be happy.
But right now,

49:11.983 --> 49:13.215
I don't give two shits.

49:14.719 --> 49:16.719
This is an uncomfortable
discourse for you.

49:17.555 --> 49:19.722
It's okay. I get it.

49:19.724 --> 49:22.358
Your uncomfortable
talking about the craft.

49:22.360 --> 49:24.560
I thought we were actors.

49:24.562 --> 49:26.195
Look, we are
two different actors.

49:26.197 --> 49:28.664
Me not talking about it,
doesn't mean I don't want to.

49:28.666 --> 49:31.067
But it may mean I don't wanna
talk about it with you.

49:31.069 --> 49:33.102
Yes. Yes!

49:33.104 --> 49:34.537
That's what I'm talking about.

49:34.539 --> 49:36.472
This right here, I felt it.

49:36.474 --> 49:39.375
Did you feel that? I mean,
we could be that. Right now.

49:39.377 --> 49:41.477
Confined. At wit's end.

49:42.647 --> 49:44.080
Have you spoken with Trumbo?

49:46.084 --> 49:47.183
No.

49:47.185 --> 49:49.586
Well, I phoned him.

49:49.587 --> 49:51.988
Now he seemed very open
to the idea of working with me

49:51.990 --> 49:53.589
on Dega's character.
Molding him.

49:53.591 --> 49:55.191
Really? You phoned Trumbo?

49:55.193 --> 49:56.759
Of course. I got thoughts.

49:56.761 --> 49:58.594
-He's got thoughts.
- Yeah, I got thoughts.

49:58.596 --> 50:00.262
I got ideas.

50:00.264 --> 50:03.499
Right now, Dega's character
is very thin.

50:03.501 --> 50:04.700
And you'd like to work
with the writer

50:04.702 --> 50:06.235
to make him bigger?

50:06.237 --> 50:07.436
Make him more...

50:08.639 --> 50:09.739
fleshed out.

50:10.675 --> 50:13.710
Fascinating.

50:13.711 --> 50:16.746
Yeah. Well, in Cherrier's book,
Dega is just a minor character.

50:16.748 --> 50:19.115
So you think
you should be bigger?

50:19.117 --> 50:21.717
Well, I think
he should be more...

50:21.719 --> 50:23.786
-Fleshed out.
-Fleshed out, exactly.

50:25.623 --> 50:28.024
Sounds like you've given this
a lot of thought.

50:28.026 --> 50:29.658
I have.

50:29.660 --> 50:31.060
You haven't signed yet, though.

50:31.062 --> 50:32.628
No.

50:32.630 --> 50:34.497
Why the cold feet?

50:34.499 --> 50:36.265
I'm just weighing my options.

50:36.267 --> 50:38.601
Trying to figure out
what works best for me.

50:39.604 --> 50:40.803
- Of course.
-Yeah.

50:42.407 --> 50:45.174
Do you know that
I did an entire film

50:45.810 --> 50:47.209
in Italian?

50:48.646 --> 50:49.745
I did not.

50:50.815 --> 50:53.149
That was a challenge.

50:53.151 --> 50:55.685
And that's
what I'm talking about.

50:55.686 --> 50:58.220
Maybe on this film,
we do the whole thing in French.

50:58.222 --> 51:00.289
Yeah, I don't think
the studio would go for that.

51:00.291 --> 51:02.425
Well, who cares
what the studios think?

51:02.427 --> 51:04.460
I mean, what do the studios
really know anyway?

51:04.462 --> 51:06.429
I mean, the studio
wouldn't know real art,

51:06.431 --> 51:09.465
if it walked right up to 'em,
kicked 'em square in the nuts.

51:11.469 --> 51:13.235
Has Freddie talked to you
about First Artists?

51:13.237 --> 51:14.303
He is my agent.

51:16.140 --> 51:17.339
And are you on board?

51:18.543 --> 51:21.444
Not that it's your business,
but not yet.

51:21.446 --> 51:23.179
Well, it could be my business.

51:23.181 --> 51:25.081
It could be
our business together.

51:25.083 --> 51:27.450
Think about it.

51:27.451 --> 51:29.818
A production company
completely run by the artists.

51:31.455 --> 51:33.088
You know, when something sounds
too good to be true,

51:33.091 --> 51:34.156
it usually is.

51:34.158 --> 51:36.592
Streisand, Poitier...

51:39.230 --> 51:41.130
-Newman.
- Newman.

51:41.132 --> 51:42.398
Exactly.

51:42.399 --> 51:43.665
Why should we be left out
in the cold?

51:43.668 --> 51:45.267
Who said we would be?

51:45.269 --> 51:46.635
There's other ways
to get control.

51:46.637 --> 51:47.837
I got plenty of juice.

51:48.673 --> 51:50.172
That's not what I hear.

51:51.275 --> 51:52.675
Be careful what you hear.

51:52.677 --> 51:54.610
People talk in this town, Steve.

51:54.612 --> 51:56.545
I mean, your racing picture's
in trouble.

51:56.547 --> 51:59.315
And Solar's deal,
it's on the ropes.

52:00.218 --> 52:01.851
What is this?

52:01.852 --> 52:03.485
You don't need my permission,
not to play Dega.

52:03.488 --> 52:06.322
Not to join First Artists.

52:06.324 --> 52:09.592
Are you looking for approval?
'Cause I'm not your daddy.

52:09.594 --> 52:11.260
Or maybe you're just looking
for a little insurance,

52:11.262 --> 52:12.328
is that it?

52:12.730 --> 52:14.497
Maybe.

52:14.499 --> 52:17.133
I'm trying to wrap my head
around the idea

52:17.135 --> 52:18.834
of being a team player.

52:18.836 --> 52:21.770
And if Steve McQueen
can be a team player,

52:21.772 --> 52:23.205
I guess I could, too.

52:25.343 --> 52:26.809
Well, I don't know
what to tell you, kid.

52:28.379 --> 52:30.446
All my decisions come
in due time.

52:32.416 --> 52:33.482
This is good.

52:34.519 --> 52:35.651
It feels right.

52:37.288 --> 52:39.155
I think I wanna play Dega.

52:39.157 --> 52:40.256
I think you're a good actor.

52:42.727 --> 52:44.894
You may even be great,
but make no mistake,

52:44.896 --> 52:47.263
I don't care if it's Trumbo,

52:47.265 --> 52:49.832
Shaffner or anybody else
blowing smoke up your ass.

52:51.569 --> 52:54.336
That set will be mine,
you got that?

54:28.366 --> 54:29.431
A lot of actors I see

54:29.433 --> 54:30.933
worry about losing
the spotlight.

54:31.936 --> 54:33.402
Never been a concern.

54:34.672 --> 54:35.738
Until now.

54:39.977 --> 54:41.310
Tell me about France.

54:42.913 --> 54:44.780
Tell me about Le Mans.

54:44.782 --> 54:46.515
They took the film away from me.

54:47.451 --> 54:48.517
Who did?

54:49.287 --> 54:50.552
The suits...

54:50.554 --> 54:51.854
at Cinema Center.

54:53.057 --> 54:54.323
The producers,

54:55.326 --> 54:57.326
Stulbarg and Bob Rosen.

54:58.596 --> 55:00.796
-Friends?
-No. Not really.

55:01.599 --> 55:02.765
Lost them too, though.

55:04.869 --> 55:06.302
Misunderstandings.

55:06.737 --> 55:07.836
Betrayals.

55:09.707 --> 55:11.340
My business partner, Bob,

55:12.710 --> 55:14.510
then it was Stan, my agent.

55:15.579 --> 55:18.047
Where were they
when I needed them, huh?

55:18.049 --> 55:20.082
Nowhere I'll tell you, so...

55:20.084 --> 55:21.350
...cut them loose.

55:23.387 --> 55:24.453
Have you seen it?

55:25.389 --> 55:26.455
I did.

55:27.958 --> 55:29.024
And?

55:30.528 --> 55:32.461
There were problems.

55:32.463 --> 55:36.432
We had a lot of guys, good guys,
looking to crack that story.

55:36.434 --> 55:38.867
We had John, directing,
Sturges. You know him?

55:39.503 --> 55:41.437
I know of him.

55:41.439 --> 55:43.038
Did three pictures with him

55:43.040 --> 55:44.473
and he walked out on me.

55:45.676 --> 55:46.875
Walked out on a movie?

55:46.877 --> 55:47.976
No. On me.

55:52.016 --> 55:53.482
Would you agree that

55:53.484 --> 55:54.883
films are
a collaborative effort?

55:54.885 --> 55:56.819
No. Not on Le Mans.

55:56.821 --> 55:57.986
This was my vision.

55:59.023 --> 56:00.356
I knew what I wanted.

56:01.759 --> 56:03.726
That's not always
easily expressed.

56:05.062 --> 56:06.662
I don't know how clear
I gotta be.

56:10.901 --> 56:12.968
Sounds like
a stressful situation.

56:12.970 --> 56:14.870
And then some, Doc.

56:17.742 --> 56:19.608
So I imagine, the probable
outcome for the film

56:19.610 --> 56:20.676
is not good.

56:20.978 --> 56:22.111
Nope.

56:24.749 --> 56:26.949
As a man that is judged
by his peers...

56:28.085 --> 56:30.386
based on reviews
and box office receipts,

56:30.388 --> 56:31.854
this must be a bitter pill.

56:33.758 --> 56:35.524
Le Mans
was your passion project.

56:36.627 --> 56:38.127
A convergence
of the two things that

56:38.129 --> 56:40.496
you pretty much
dedicated your life to.

56:42.433 --> 56:45.768
Any accolades or awards
would mean affirmation.

56:45.770 --> 56:47.870
Affirmation of your vision.

56:47.872 --> 56:49.838
I got awards, nominations.

56:49.840 --> 56:50.939
Don't need them.

56:52.143 --> 56:53.609
An Academy Award?

56:53.611 --> 56:54.710
Nominated.

56:55.946 --> 56:57.012
Once.

57:03.020 --> 57:04.787
You're a box office champion.

57:04.789 --> 57:06.622
Right.

57:06.624 --> 57:08.657
You have a strong drive
to win, Steve.

57:09.960 --> 57:11.460
And both awards and...

57:13.030 --> 57:14.997
box office receipts

57:14.999 --> 57:17.433
constitute the pinnacle
of winning in Hollywood.

57:18.702 --> 57:21.003
You didn't hope
to achieve this with Le Mans?

57:22.706 --> 57:25.174
Look, you want every movie
to be a success.

57:28.212 --> 57:30.679
Even if Le Mans
succeeds at the box office

57:30.681 --> 57:32.181
or at the Academy Awards,

57:33.884 --> 57:36.685
I don't think you're
gonna consider it a success.

57:36.687 --> 57:37.853
No, I won't.

57:39.557 --> 57:41.457
Because it was taken
away from you.

57:41.459 --> 57:42.558
It's not your film.

57:45.796 --> 57:47.596
You sacrificed a lot
for this film.

57:48.999 --> 57:50.132
More than you know.

57:52.069 --> 57:53.168
I want to know.

57:54.805 --> 57:56.905
I want you to tell me,
that's why we're here.

57:56.907 --> 57:58.774
We're here
because Neile asked me to.

58:02.780 --> 58:03.879
It was a long shoot.

58:05.549 --> 58:06.615
An arduous shoot.

58:08.719 --> 58:11.253
Women,
drugs fill the down time?

58:13.591 --> 58:14.656
It didn't hurt.

58:23.234 --> 58:24.500
So,

58:25.236 --> 58:26.502
that night.

58:32.076 --> 58:33.876
I don't wanna talk
about that night.

58:35.679 --> 58:37.679
We've come a long way
here today, Steve.

58:39.183 --> 58:40.949
I think we need
to talk about it.

58:45.723 --> 58:48.290
What did you do that night
at the chateau in France?

58:51.929 --> 58:54.229
Steve, what did
you do that night?

59:09.880 --> 59:11.580
I put a gun in my wife's head.

59:14.051 --> 59:16.051
Why did you put a gun
to your wife's head?

59:20.024 --> 59:22.057
Because she told me
she had an affair.

59:24.728 --> 59:27.195
She already knew
of your indiscretions?

59:27.197 --> 59:29.698
Yeah. I always confessed.

59:31.335 --> 59:32.868
But that
only helped you...

59:33.270 --> 59:34.336
with your guilt.

59:40.878 --> 59:41.777
What else did you do?

59:45.783 --> 59:46.848
Steve?

59:52.256 --> 59:54.623
I hurt her.

59:59.229 --> 01:00:00.362
I hurt my wife.

01:00:01.765 --> 01:00:02.931
I keep hurting her.

01:00:09.173 --> 01:00:10.639
Why would you hurt your wife?

01:00:17.715 --> 01:00:19.081
I can't stop.

01:00:25.089 --> 01:00:26.188
Tell me about him.

01:00:26.924 --> 01:00:28.290
I already have.

01:00:28.292 --> 01:00:29.925
-Tell me again.
-No!

01:00:31.662 --> 01:00:33.362
Where did you meet him?

01:00:33.364 --> 01:00:34.796
Where did you meet him? Hm?

01:00:34.798 --> 01:00:36.164
Stop. Don't do this to yourself.

01:00:39.069 --> 01:00:40.335
Where did you meet him?

01:00:40.337 --> 01:00:42.704
Steve, stop, please.

01:00:42.706 --> 01:00:44.306
